Description: Make an estimated plan of how the workload will be spread across the allowed timeframe
Create a Basic C Lexer that can identify most of the trivial tokens in the C language
The Lexer can identify complex regular expressions and can successfully read and tokenize provided C source codes
The Parser can parse trivial expressions/statements and most importantly have a working communication between Bison and Flex
Be able to group tokens that are syntactically legal and parse an Abstract Syntax Tree
Be confident that the C parser is at the required final level of required complexity. Test it extensively to see what has been achieved
Need to learn basic Python syntax in order to be able to write a C to Python Translator
Using the Lexer and the Parser implemented, create an Abstract Syntax Tree to Python from C
Using principles learned from the CodeGen lab, structure the implementation of the Abstract Syntax Tree to MIPS I assembly
The CodeGen at least works for all of the basic cases and hopefully even more
Verify the CodeGen works for most of the cases and hopefully (near) all
Make up a formal TestBench to test extensively the Compiler and Translator
